-- Chalco Shares Drop in Shanghai After It Posts $17.7 Million Quarterly Loss
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-26T01:30:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/chalco-shares-drop-in-shanghai-after-it-posts-17-7-million-quarterly-loss.html
Aluminum Corp. of China Ltd.’s
shares fell 0.5 percent to 12.79 yuan in premarket Shanghai
trading after the reported a consecutive quarterly loss.  Chalco, China’s largest producer of the lightweight metal,
had a net loss of 117.8 million yuan ($17.7 million) for the
three months ended Sept. 30.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
